What you need to know:

Famous or infamous victory? Brazil played true to their philosophy: happy, free-flowing and exquisitely artistic football, while Italy were dour but effective, and their style won the World CupAnd the team that lost, whose high aesthetic standards hacked back to the legendary teams of the 1950s, 1960s and 1970s, mourned the ending of a way of life. Millions of their fans across the world mourned, too. For the beautiful game was no more